  <metadata>
    <name>Wetherlam from Tilberthwaite</name>
    <bounds minlat="54.3825395" minlon="-3.0976059" maxlat="54.4059900" maxlon="-3.0700005" />
  </metadata>
  <rte>
    <name>Wetherlam from Tilberthwaite</name>
    <desc>Wetherlam is often included as part of a horseshoe starting with Coniston Old Man or, from Little Langdale, in a circuit including Swirl How and Wet Side Edge. It is, however, a fine mountain in its own right and this Lake District walk of moderate length from the delightful hamlet of Tilberthwaite covers some varied terrain. </desc>
	<author>Copyright Walking Britain</author>
	<url>www.walkingbritain.co.uk/walk-2033-description</url>
